(void) - load

Detailed Description

ActiveRecord provides some required and optional methods for database objects to implement. By implementing these methods, an object is following the active record design pattern.

Member Function Documentation

- (void) load  

Loads all of the object properties into memory. Generally reserved for when all of the object is needed.
